He was replaced by Brazilian defender Dante, who was part of the international side that lost 7-1 to Germany in their World Cup semi-final earlier this summer. 

Wednesday night's result helped Dortmund inflict an early psychological blow on bitter rivals Bayern.

Hendrikh Mkhitaryan put Dortmund ahead in the 23rd minute and new signing Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang doubled their lead in the 62nd minute.

